Executive Profile
Mark S. Ain  Founder and Director, Kronos IncorporatedAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships74--
Background

		Mr. Mark S. Ain is Founder and Member of Board of Directors at Kronos Incorporated. Mr. Ain was Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of the Board at the firm. He founded the firm in 1997. Mr. Ain serves as a Corporate Advisor of Perillon Software, Inc. He serves as an Advisor of SpaceClaim Corporation and has served as a Director of the firm. Mr. Ain was an Advisor of Castile Ventures, where he offered guidance and operational insights to its portfolio companies, drawing ... on over three decades of experience navigating the challenges faced by growing businesses and on a deep familiarity with the software industry. He has been associated with Castile since its foundation and his charter expanded on an informal advisory role that has developed over a number of years. Prior to Kronos, Mr. Ain had a stint at Digital Equipment Corporation both in product development and as a Sales Training Director. He was also employed at a small market research firm. From 1974 to 1977, Mr. Ain served as a Consultant, specifically in strategic planning, product development, market research and organizational development. He serves as a Member of Strategic Advisory Board at Artemis Capital Partners. He serves as a Director of the Walker School, Simon School at University of Rochester and YMCA since 1997. He has been a Director of KVH Industries Inc. since 1997 and has been its Lead Director since August 2, 2007. Mr. Ain serves as Board Member of LTX-Credence Corporation. He has been an Independent Director of Xcerra Corporation since September 2001 and its Lead Independent Director since June 2010. He has been a Director of SiMPore Inc. since June 2009. Mr. Ain serves as a Director of several public, private and non-profit charitable organizations and is a speaker at financial and executive conferences and various graduate business schools. He served as an Independent Director of VeruTEK Technologies, Inc. since October 12, 2007. He served as a Director of Park Electrochemical Corporation since 1998. Mr. Ain holds an M.B.A. in Marketing and Organizational Behavior from the Simon School at the University of Rochester and a B.S. in Electrical Engineering from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.Read Full Background




