Mark Ain
Full-Time MBA, Class of 1967

Executive Chairman,
Kronos Inc.


	Mark Stuart Ain ’67S (MBA) was the recipient of the 2005 Simon Business School Distinguished Alumnus Award. He is Executive Chairman of Kronos Inc., based in Chelmsford, Mass., the industry-leading workforce management company he founded in 1977.

	Under Mr. Ain’s guidance, Kronos has achieved a growth and profitability track record among software companies that is second only to Microsoft’s. It now has 2,700 employees in 67 offices worldwide. Mr. Ain is recognized as an outstanding entrepreneur in New England and has received a number of regional awards for his achievements.

	Over many years, Mark Ain has communicated his passion for entrepreneurship to Simon Business School students—as well as to audiences in many other educational and industry settings—giving generously of his time in formal presentations and informal conversation. He has encouraged potential MBA candidates to attend the School, mentored Simon students and supported the School financially. As a member of the Alumni Advisory Committee and, currently, of the Executive Advisory Committee, Mr. Ain has participated in the setting of priorities and strategies for the Simon Business School.













      Mark Ain
      Ain
      
	Mark Ain has communicated his passion for entrepreneurship to Simon Business School students—as well as to audiences in many other educational and industry settings. Ain has encouraged potential MBA candidates to attend the School and mentored many Simon students.

