AIN Special Reports



Each year AIN’s editors are sent into the field to produce in-depth special reports on certain subject areas from around business aviation. From reviewing new technologies in cockpit avionics to our annual Product Support and FBO Surveys, these reports are longer and more comprehensive than our normal news items from elsewhere on the site. Stay tuned as a new report is published almost every month.
Viewing these reports require Adobe Reader be installed on your device. If it’s not currently installed, click here to download.
 




  
 Jul 13, 2017 - 11:03 AM 
 Civil Supersonics 
 Concorde is a museum piece, but the allure of speed could spell success for one or more of these projects.  

  
 Jul 3, 2017 - 8:32 AM 
 AIN Special Report Completions and Refurbishment 
 OEMs are making the cabins of new aircraft more customizable, and completions centers offer numerous options for aircraft refreshment.  

  
 Jun 14, 2017 - 11:09 AM 
 Industry Prepares Widebody Entries as Market ‘Rebalances’  
 Various derivative programs coming to fruition.  

  
 Jun 5, 2017 - 3:03 PM 
 Aircraft Insurance 2017 
 Proper coverage and awareness of regulations are key  

  
 Sponsor Content 
 Jun 1, 2017 - 9:00 AM 
 Industry Insights: Maintenance, Repair  & Overhaul—a Sector in Upgrade Mode 
 Business aviation depends on maintenance, repair, and overhaul (MRO) providers for safe and reliable operations.  

  
 Sponsor Content 
 May 12, 2017 - 10:15 AM 
 The Registry of Aruba: The Sky is No Longer the Limit 
 The Registry of Aruba offers aircraft owners benefits including expedited registration, efficient tax planning, and a highly skilled team.   

  
 May 7, 2017 - 12:36 PM 
 GA Manufacturers Expand Their Global Footprint 
 The number of general aviation manufacturers owned by non-U.S. investors is surprisingly large.  

  
 May 5, 2017 - 7:36 AM 
 New Aerospace Technology and Business Aviation 
 Fly-by-wire, integrated interfaces and more extensive electrification are found on most new jets…automated aircraft could be coming.  

  
 Mar 13, 2017 - 2:49 AM 
 Training in the Icon A5 Amphibious LSA 
 Does the pilot training program match Icon Aircraft’s ambitious goals? AIN’s Matt Thurber travels to Vacaville to find the answer.  

  
 Mar 9, 2017 - 2:44 AM 
 Business Aviation and the Environment 
 Infrastructure, technology and alternative fuels are on the industry's radar to reduce environment impact, and save money.  

